It filters each message if it contains forbidden characters like [B]Spanish [/B]("ñ", "¿", "¡", etc.), [B]Nordic [/B]("ø", "å"), [B]Slavic [/B]("ę", "ł", "ż", etc.), [B]French [/B]("é", "à", "œ", etc.), [B]German [/B](ä, ö, ü, etc.) or [B]Cyrillic [/B](б", "г", "ж", etc.).

You are also able to define your own filtered words or characters. For example, it could be also used to filter swear words not detected by ESO  itself.

[FONT=Arial Black][SIZE=5][COLOR=Orange][B]Settings[/B][/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT]

If you have the LibAddonMenu-2.0 installed, you will have access to the settings menu to define your own filters and set or unset the filter for predefined characters.

[FONT=Arial Black][SIZE=5][COLOR=Orange][B]Commands[/B][/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT][LIST]
[*][B]/cmc[/B] main command to open setting menu or show current settings
[*][B]/cmc filter[/B] shows the defined custom characters
[*][B]/cmc custom[/B] toggles the custom character filter
[*][B]/cmc cyrillic[/B] toggles the Cyrillic character filter
[*][B]/cmc french[/B] toggles the French character filter
[*][B]/cmc german[/B] toggles the German character filter
[*][B]/cmc nordic[/B] toggles the Nordiccharacter filter
[*][B]/cmc slavic[/B] toggles the Slavic character filter
[*][B]/cmc spanish[/B] toggles the Spanish character filter[/LIST][FONT=Arial Black][SIZE=5][COLOR=Orange][B]Compatability[/B][/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT]

It is tested and created to work with [B][URL="https://www.esoui.com/downloads/info93-pChat.html"][COLOR=orange]pChat[/COLOR][/URL][/B] or the default chat system.
